		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Evil</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Evil_(disambiguation)" title="Evil (disambiguation)">Evil (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/wiki/File:GustaveDoreParadiseLostSatanProfile.jpg" class="image" title="In Christianity, Satan is considered the being most infested with evil in all of creation."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/GustaveDoreParadiseLostSatanProfile.jpg/200px-GustaveDoreParadiseLostSatanProfile.jpg" width="200" height="227" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:GustaveDoreParadiseLostSatanProfile.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
In <a href="/wiki/Christianity" title="Christianity">Christianity</a>, <a href="/wiki/Satan" title="Satan">Satan</a> is considered the being most infested with evil in all of <a href="/wiki/Creation" title="Creation">creation</a>.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Evil</b>, in many cultures, is a broad term used to describe intentional negative moral acts or thoughts that are cruel, unjust or selfish. Evil is usually <a href="/wiki/Good_and_evil" title="Good and evil">contrasted with <i>good</i></a>, which describes acts that are kind, just or unselfish. In some religions, evil is an active force, often personified as an entity such as <a href="/wiki/Satan" title="Satan">Satan</a> or <a href="/wiki/Ahriman" title="Ahriman" class="mw-redirect">Ahriman</a>.</p>
